{
  "texts": [
    "Logistic function fitting parameters for various datasets.",
    "The table reports the α (growth rate), β (point of half-saturation), and SI (Speed Index) values, which are derived from fitting the data for each platform into a logistic function.",
    "SI measures the normalized area under the curve.",
    "Root mean square error (RMSE) quantifies the model accuracy in fitting data.",
    "The smaller the value, the closer the predictions are to the observations."
  ]
